doc_summary_long: Exclusive: Draft regulations seen by the Guardian reveal the European commission wants to prohibit the insecticides that cause 'acute risks to bees' The world's most widely used insecticides would be banned from all fields across Europe under draft regulations from the European commission, seen by the Guardian. The documents are the first indication that the powerful commission wants a complete ban and cite 'high acute risks to bees'. A ban could be in place this year if the proposals are approved by a majority of EU member states.
doc_summary_short: Exclusive: Draft regulations seen by the Guardian reveal the European commission wants to prohibit the insecticides that cause 'acute risks to bees'
doc_title: Europe poised for total ban on bee-harming pesticides
